<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="358" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1688,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,354,1688,1714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Diagnosis. Adult.</emphasis>
As for the genus. No characters were detected allowing a general separation of reared postlarval instars of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Southcott" authorityYear="1995" box="[414,531,1725,1750]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Erythraeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Zaracarus">
<emphasis box="[414,531,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Zaracarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from postlarval instars of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" box="[979,1103,1724,1750]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Erythraeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[979,1103,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Erythraeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1688,1931]" box="[199,812,1760,1787]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,362,1760,1786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Deutonymph.</emphasis>
As for the genus (See comment above).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1688,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1796,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Larva</emphasis>
(after 
<bibRefCitation author="Southcott, R. V." box="[351,526,1796,1823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" pagination="223 - 228" refId="ref12790" refString="Southcott, R. V. (1995) A new larval erythraeine mite (Acarina: Erythraeidae) from Spain. Acarologia, 36 (3), 223 - 228." type="journal article" year="1995">Southcott 1995</bibRefCitation>
, with modifications by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fain, A. &amp; Ripka, G." box="[798,1024,1796,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref11661" refString="Fain, A. &amp; Ripka, G. (1998) A new larval Erythraeidae (Acari) from Hungary. International Journal of Acarology, 24 (1), 41 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647959808684125" type="journal article" year="1998">Fain &amp; Ripka 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" box="[1137,1261,1796,1822]" class="Arachnida" family="Erythraeidae" genus="Erythraeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1137,1261,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Erythraeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larva. Anterior sensilla below 50 µm in length, with expanded base, situated in pouch-like structures. Basis of setae AL smooth and thin or setulose and widened. Two or three basifemoral setae on legs I–III.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,636,1904,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" type="distribution">
